<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4001] Improve Kafka Streams Join Semantics (KIP-77)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4001</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kafka Streams supports three types of joins:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;KStream-KStream&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;KStream-KTable&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;KTable-KTable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, Kafka Streams supports the join variant, namely&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;inner join&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;left join&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;outer join&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Not all combination of &quot;type&quot; and &quot;variant&quot; are supported.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The problem is, that the semantics of the different joins do use different semantics (and are thus inconsistent).&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With this ticket, we want to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;introduce unique semantics over all joins&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;improve handling of &quot;null&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add missing inner KStream-KTable join&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See KIP-76 for more details: &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-76%3A+Improve+Kafka+Streams+Join+Semantics&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-76%3A+Improve+Kafka+Streams+Join+Semantics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
